claim.claim-text:
A method of handling random access response for a network in a wireless communication system, characterized by the method comprising:
assigning a first random access preamble for a first mobile device in a first component carrier of a plurality of component carriers (810);
receiving a second random access preamble from a second mobile device at a second component carrier, wherein the second random access preamble is identical to the first random access preamble (820);
receiving no assigned first random access preamble from the first mobile device at the first component carrier during a period of time (830); and
responding no random access response to the first and second random access preambles (840).
